<span id="v.iv.iv.iv-p10"></span> The reader will remember that
Tertullian is here arguing on Marcion’s ground, according to whom the
Creator’s Christ, the Christ predicted through the O.T., was yet to
come. Marcion’s Christ, however, had proved himself so weak to stem the
Creator’s course, that he had no means really of checking the Creator’s
Christ from coming. It had been better, adds Tertullian, if Marcion’s
Christ had waited for the Creator’s Christ to have first appeared.

